  "time_ut": 1660563123,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca \u0db7\u0da7\u0dba\u0ddd \u0db6\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dc1\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0d85\u0db7\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dba",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Navy Marines Multilateral Maritime Exercise",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lankan Navy Marines, which participated in the multilateral maritime exercise organized by the US Navy's Pacific Fleet, recently returned after completing the successful exercise in the Pacific Ocean, focusing on the area around the Hawaiian Islands and Southern California of the United States of America.",
        "To participate in this multi-party maritime exercise, the Sri Lanka Navy Marine team consisting of 50 officers and sailors left for Australia in a special aircraft belonging to the Royal Australian Air Force, where after participating in joint training exercises in Townville, Australia and in the Canberra ship of the Royal Australian Navy, the Pacific Participated in the maritime exercise held in the ocean region.",
        "For this exercise Sri Lanka, Australia, Brunei, Canada, Chile, Colombia, Denmark, Ecuador, France, Germany, India, Indonesia, Israel, Japan, Malaysia, Mexico, Netherlands, New Zealand, Peru, Republic of Korea, Philippines, Singapore, Thailand , Tonga State, United Kingdom and United States of America, including 38 warships from 26 countries, 03 submarines, 09 land forces, 170 war planes and about 25000 military personnel participated.",
        "The Sri Lanka Navy Marines participated in a one-week field training program together with members of the Royal Australian Army in Townville, Australia, where they received a range of training including small arms handling and shooting exercises, urban operations, combat training and field signals.",
        "While the Sri Lankan Navy Marines sailed to Hawaii by the Royal Australian Navy ship Canberra, they gained extensive knowledge of operational planning including dispersal of personnel, urban warfare, ship landing exercises and amphibious exercises together with the Australian and Tongan troops."
      ],
